This paper deals with the optimization of spectrum access in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves modeling and analysis of the network performance, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms for optimization, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR).
